Gold Prizes Awarded to Kimilsungia and Kimjongilia 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 14 (KCNA) -- Immortal flowers Kimilsungia and Kimjongilia created a great stir at the 2006 Shenyang World Horticultural Expo in China.
 The expo held from April 30 to the end of October brought together many horticultural organizations from at least 20 countries and regions including Netherlands, Germany, France and Canada. Thousands of species of beautiful and rare flowers and plants were presented to the expo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The recent expo was different from those held before in the manner of show. The participating organizations laid up gardens reflecting the characteristic feature of their countries and nations in the designated portions of land and built structures and annexes of diverse styles that match their gardens on the basis of their horticultural technique and standards, while putting on display their typical flowers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Officials and floricultural experts of the Korean Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia Committee exhibited Kimilsungias and Kimjongilias at the "Rose Garden" which had been specially provided by the sponsor side. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They built the "Korean Garden" in a peculiar and splendid manner to meet the need of architecture of Korean style and the principle of laying out parks with the help of creators and designers of the Mansudae Art Studio and the Paektusan Architectural Institute. As a result, the "Korean Garden" attracted the attention of world horticultural experts from the first day of the expo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The organizing committee of the expo awarded gold prizes, the top prize of the expo, and diplomas to Kimilsungia and Kimjongilia each. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It also presented the best prize (cup) of the expo, diploma and honorary certificate to the "Korean Garden," gold prizes and diplomas to the festive gate and group sculpture of children of the "Korean Garden," silver prizes to the pavilion and fountain and a bronze prize to the Korean wing of the expo. The DPRK thus received eight prizes something unprecedented in the history of world horticultural expo.

South Koreans Called upon to Shatter Plot of Pro-U.S. Conservatives to Seize "Power" 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 14 (KCNA) -- The south Korean people from all walks of life should shatter the plot of the pro-U.S. conservative forces to close their ranks and grab "power" with a great alliance of anti-conservatives and completely eliminate the treacherous forces in order to avert a war and defend peace in this land and glorify the June 15 era. A spokesman for the Central Committee of the Democratic Front for the Reunification of the Fatherland urged this in a statement on Nov. 13.
 It went on: The "National League of New Right," a new umbrella organization of pro-U.S. conservative forces in south Korea, held a "ceremony to mark its first anniversary" and "a plenary meeting of its members" on Nov. 9. Speakers there cried out for "forming all-people alliance" to seize "power" through the next presidential election. The so-called presidential candidates from the Grand National Party of south Korea in their "congratulatory addresses" openly disclosed their wild ambition to grab "power." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is part of the premeditated moves to set up a pro-U.S. conservative regime by forming an alliance of pro-U.S. conservative forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 "All-people alliance" much touted by them is a political collusion to grab "power," going against the trend of the June 15 era, and a sinister treacherous, undemocratic and anti-reunification alliance of pro-U.S. conservative forces to put again the south Korean people under the dark dictatorial rule. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
It is as clear as noonday that if the pro-U.S. conservative forces are allowed to come to power under the manipulation of the U.S. they will halt the process of independence and democratization in south Korea, scrap the June 15 joint declaration and bring disasters of a nuclear war to all Koreans. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The GNP and the "National League of New Right" and other pro-U.S. conservatives are working hard to win the favor of people in a bid to gratify their greed for "power" but they can never cover up their true colors as a group of stooges of the U.S., a wicked enemy of peace and reunification, a principal enemy of democratization and a group of quislings. They are fated to meet only shameful destruction.

U.S. Sanctions against DPRK under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 14 (KCNA) -- More than 60 civic and public organizations of south Korea including the Reunification Solidarity and the "National People's Solidarity" called a press conference in front of the building of the "Ministry of Foreign Affairs and Trade" in Seoul on Nov. 7 and vehemently denounced the U.S. sanctions against the DPRK, according to the south Korean Internet papers "Thongil News" and "Chammalo."
 Speakers at the press conference referred to the fact that the south Korean and U.S. authorities held a "vice-ministerial strategic dialogue" in Seoul and talked about "sanctions" and "blockade" against the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  They charged that the U.S. refused to have dialogue with the north even before the ink of the signature to the joint statement of the 4th round of the six-party talks (September 19 joint statement) was dry and has persistently pursued its hostile policy towards the north and recently worsened the situation of the Korean Peninsula with its sanctions against the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then a press release was read out. It noted that the U.S. oppression and sanctions against the north and the drive for implementing the "Proliferation Security Initiative of Weapons of Mass Destruction" are putting a block on the way of resumption of the six-party talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean "government," aligning itself with the U.S. hostile policy towards the north, has driven the south-north relations into catastrophe, the release said, stressing: If the U.S. really wants peace in the Korean Peninsula through dialogue, it should lift all sorts of sanctions against the north at once.

Japan's Frantic Agitation of Militarism Blasted 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 14 (KCNA) -- Some days ago, the new Japanese minister of Education, Culture, Sports, Science and Technology did not bother to call on the educational institutions to hoist Hinomaru and sing Kimigayo, asserting that it is the duty of the teachers to do so. 
 Rodong Sinmun Tuesday observes in a signed commentary in this regard: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His vociferation glaringly reveals the militarist nature of the Abe regime and is a very disturbing agitation of militarism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 By imposing the hoisting of Hinomaru and the singing of Kimigayo upon schools the Japanese reactionaries seek to imbue the young Japanese with pride in the history of the Japanese imperialists' aggression, longing for militarism and the resolution to exact revenge for their past defeat in a bid to make the Japanese society veer to the Right and rush headlong into militarization. It is their calculation that this would help them realize their wild militarist ambition left unaccomplished for several decades. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The present Japanese chief executive, when interviewed by CNN a few days ago, expressed Japan's intention to revise the constitution during the tenure of his office. And the director general of the Japan Defence Agency cried out that now is the time to rewrite Article 9 of the constitution which stipulates the war renouncement, etc. All these outcries let loose by the Japanese reactionaries were promoted by their calculation that the time has come to achieve their militarist aim unhindered. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If their militarist moves are overlooked, this will not only seriously endanger the peace and stability in Northeast Asia but allow Japan to repeat such tragic history in which the Japanese imperialists ignited a war of aggression against Asian countries scores of years ago, murdering civilians and destroying everything, warns the commentary.

Rodong Sinmun on Imperialists' Ambition for Aggression 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 14 (KCNA) -- Imperialism is looking for new targets of aggression and plunder to gratify the unlimited greed of monopoly capital as its sphere of domination and influence gains in scope. Rodong Sinmun Tuesday observes this in a signed article. Citing facts, the article notes that the above-said development is clearly proved by the brigandish acts of the U.S. 
 The U.S. imperialists are working harder than ever before to realize their wild ambition for world domination. To this end they are putting spurs to arms expansion and war preparations, prioritizing the pursuance of the policy of strength as a main lever for realizing the ambition. They are stretching their tentacles of aggression even to outer space. The spearhead of their aggressive and reactionary world strategy is directed to the anti-imperialist and independent countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists' ambition for aggression finds its vivid manifestation in its policy toward the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They are attaching great military and strategic importance to the Korean Peninsula in executing their policy of strength to dominate the world. They are set to use south Korea and Japan as springboards from which to fight a war against the DPRK and other countries and strongholds to maintain their system for dominating the Asia-Pacific region. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What merits a more serious attention is the fact that the U.S. is contemplating the modification of "CONPLAN" called "OPLAN 5029" as a "military operational plan" to cope with a contingency on the Korean Peninsula and blustering that it is ready to carry it out any moment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is beyond doubt that the U.S. is poised to ignite a war in Korea and launch a world war with it as a momentum. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists are the aggressors who interfere in the internal affairs of Korea and war fanatics keen on provoking a new Korean war to realize its ambition for aggression against the DPRK.

Vigorous Campaign for Model Teacher in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 14 (KCNA) -- A campaign for winning the title of "October 8 Model Teacher" is being vigorously launched in the education field of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 The campaign is aimed at drastically improving the standard of teaching and the training of talents by making teachers raise their responsibility and role. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This year all the universities and colleges throughout the country have pushed ahead with the campaign in close relation to the teaching work and activities for improving professors' qualification and increasing the ranks of those with academic degrees or titles, thus making a great innovation in the educational content in accordance with the requirement of the IT era. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The campaign has been briskly conducted in the field of general education, too. Thousands of educational officials and teachers have been honored with the title of "October 8 Model Teacher" in the country this year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ho Kwang Il, a department director of the Ministry of Education told KCNA that the campaign is displaying greater vitality as the days go by under the high degree of enthusiasm and interests of the educational officials and teachers across the country.
